@M_KOJO_EVENT_K60_STONEBATTLE(ARGS,ARG,ARG:1)
IF ARGS == "beginning"
	PRINTFORMDW 「The Jealousy Beneath the Earth's Crust! Parsee Mizuhashi!!!」
	PRINTFORMW
	SELECTCASE K60_ATTITUDE()
		CASE 0
			PRINTFORMW 「%K60_MASTER()%?! Well, I'm not going to hold back, even if it's you...」
		CASE 1
			PRINTFORMW 「Well well well, if it isn't %K60_MASTER()%. Time to remind you just how good I am with my hands～」
		CASE 2
			PRINTFORMW 「Wh- you?! %STONE_UKETSUKENAME%-san, is it too late to forfeit? There's no way I can win against %K60_MASTER()%...」
		CASE 3
			PRINTFORMW 「Ah, %K60_MASTER()%. I've gotten pretty good with my hands thanks to all the maintenance work I do on the bridge...」
	ENDSELECT
ELSEIF ARGS == "win"
	SELECTCASE K60_ATTITUDE()
		CASE 0
			PRINTFORMW 「Well, I wasn't expecting to beat you. You're really good, just as I expected.」
			PRINTFORMW 「Would you like to challenge the couples' division with me?」
		CASE 1
			PRINTFORMW 「I suppose I shouldn't be surprised that you're so good with your hands...」
			PRINTFORMW 「Would you like to refresh my memory tonight?」
		CASE 2
			CALL M_KOJO_COLOR_K60_JEALOUS
			PRINTFORMW 「I'm so jealous of your stone-stacking skills. Paruparu...」
			CALL M_KOJO_COLOR_K60
		CASE 3
			CALL M_KOJO_COLOR_K60_JEALOUS
			PRINTFORMW 「...」
			PRINTFORMW 「I wish I was that good at stone-stacking...」
			CALL M_KOJO_COLOR_K60
	ENDSELECT
ELSEIF ARGS == "lose"
	SELECTCASE K60_ATTITUDE()
		CASE 0
			PRINTFORMW 「I wasn't expecting to beat you, %K60_MASTER()%... but you put up quite a fight.」
			PRINTFORMW 「Would you like to challenge the couples' division with me?」
		CASE 1
			PRINTFORMW 「Oh? I won? I hope you didn't throw the match just because it was me.」
		CASE 2
			PRINTFORMW 「You let me win, didn't you?」
		CASE 3
			PRINTFORMW 「It seems that I've won. Let me know if you'd like a rematch.」
	ENDSELECT
ENDIF
RETURN 1

@M_KOJO_EVENT_K60_FAIRY_PRANK(ARGS,ARG,ARG:1)
#DIMS SELECTED_PRANK
#DIM CULPRIT
SELECTCASE ARGS
	CASE "scenarios"
		SELECTCASE RAND:2
			CASE 0
				SELECTED_PRANK = parsee_bridge_trap
			CASE 1
				SELECTED_PRANK = parsee_house_vandalism
		ENDSELECT
		RETURN 2
	CASE "prank"
		CULPRIT = VAR_OR_DEFAULT("Add_CULPRIT")
		SELECTCASE SELECTED_PRANK
			CASE "parsee_bridge_trap"
				CALL K60_GET_BRIDGE_PASSERBY()
				;hack until I can rewrite the above function to be less shit
				LOCALS = %RESULTS:5%
				PRINTFORML You and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% sneak onto the bridge half an hour before Parsee leaves to guard it.
				PRINTFORML Once there, you saw most of the way through a chunk of the floorboards.
				PRINTFORML After finishing your work, you stow your saw in a safe place and spend the next 35 minutes sightseeing in Old Hell.
				PRINTFORML Then you make your way back to the bridge and chat with Parsee, trying to act casual.
				PRINTFORML Before long, %ARTICLE(LOCALS)% steps on the unstable section of the bridge.
				PRINTFORML It collapses under %RESULTS:3% feet, and, with a yell of surprise, %RESULTS:1% falls into the river.
				PRINTFORML Parsee dives off the bridge, grabs the shocked %LOCALS%, and swims back to shore with %RESULTS:2%.
				PRINTFORML She apologizes profusely to %RESULTS:2% for not doing proper bridge maintenance, and assures %RESULTS:2% that it won't happen again.
				PRINTFORML Fortunately, the %LOCALS% doesn't seem upset, and thanks Parsee for saving %RESULTS:2% before continuing on %RESULTS:3% way.
				PRINTFORML Parsee makes her way back to the bridge and resumes her patrol.
				PRINTFORML She's grumbling to herself about how she's going to have to check the whole bridge now.
			CASE "parsee_house_vandalism"
				PRINTFORML You and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% wait for Parsee to leave her house, and then sneak in.
				PRINTFORML Once inside, you get to work.
				PRINTFORML You hide some of the portraits in her wardrobe and turn the remaining portraits upside down.
				PRINTFORML Finally, you stick a "BEWARE OF BRIDGE TROLL" sign on the door.
				PRINTFORML Snickering to yourselves, you and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% leave and hide nearby. Before long, Parsee returns home, humming something.
				PRINTFORML The humming trails off as she sees the sign. It's soon replaced by her hissing something in a language you aren't familiar with.
				PRINTFORML But judging by her tone, it's probably profanity.
				PRINTFORML Parsee rips the sign off the door, rips it in half over and over until it's nothing but confetti, and flings it away.
				PRINTFORML Then she opens the door, still swearing under her breath.
				PRINTFORML She stares into her house, temporarily shocked into silence, before she yells in rage and rushes inside.
				PRINTFORML Once you're sure she's busy fixing her portraits, you and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% make a run for it.
		ENDSELECT
		RETURN 1
	CASE "failure"
		CULPRIT = VAR_OR_DEFAULT("Add_CULPRIT")
		SELECTCASE SELECTED_PRANK
			CASE "parsee_bridge_trap"
				PRINTFORML You and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% sneak onto the bridge half an hour before Parsee leaves to guard it.
				PRINTFORML Or at least, that's what you think.
				PRINTFORML Before you can start sawing through the floorboards, a voice behind you asks what the hell you think you're doing.
				PRINTFORML You turn around to see Parsee, arms folded, and glaring daggers at you.
				PRINTFORM Before you can come up with an excuse, she 
				SELECTCASE K60_ATTITUDE()
					CASE 0, 1
						PRINTFORML yanks the saw out of your hands, taking care not to cut you with it by mistake.
						PRINTFORML Then she stares straight into your eyes, smiling coldly.
						PRINTFORML You slink away, furious at yourself. Why did you think you could prank Parsee?
						PRINTFORML She's so much older and wiser than you. You'd never be able to catch her unawares.
						PRINTFORML You're so jealous of her. And you're jealous of %CALLNAME:CULPRIT%, too.
						PRINTFORML You continue stewing in your own jealousy as you walk home. Fortunately, it wears off not long after you arrive.
					CASE 2, 3
						IF TALENT:MASTER:体型 >= 2
							PRINTFORML moves so that you're between her and the railing and punches you in the face.
							CALL RECOVER(MASTER, -750, "体力", " ")
							PRINTFORML The blow sends you reeling, but you stay on your feet.
							PRINTFORML You decide to leave before she punches you again.
						ELSEIF ABL:MASTER:戦闘能力 > ABL:TARGET:戦闘能力
							PRINTFORML moves so that you're between her and the railing and takes a swing at you.
							PRINTFORML You dodge, but the blow grazes you, and you can tell it would have probably broken your nose if it had landed.
							PRINTFORML You decide to leave before Parsee tries to punch you again.
						ELSEIF TALENT:MASTER:体型 < 0
							PRINTFORML grabs your arm and flings you into the river.
						ELSE
							PRINTFORML moves so that you're between her and the railing and punches you in the face.
							PRINTFORML The blow sends you reeling backwards. You topple over the railing and into the river.
						ENDIF
						IF TALENT:MASTER:体型 < 2 && (ABL:MASTER:戦闘能力 <= ABL:TARGET:戦闘能力)
							PRINTFORML You hit the water back-first, knocking the wind out of you.
							PRINTFORML For a brief, terrifying moment, you start to sink, before your strength comes back and you struggle to the surface.
							PRINTFORML Your head breaches the water, and you gasp for breath and shake the water out of your eyes.
							PRINTFORML Once you've caught your breath, you start swimming back to shore.
							PRINTFORML On the way, you glance at the bridge.
							PRINTFORML Parsee's leaning over the railing, watching you. She looks a little worried.
							PRINTFORML When she sees that you're not going to drown, a smug, self-satisfied grin creeps onto her face.
							PRINTFORML Looks like the joke was on you...
							DOWNBASE:MASTER:体力 += 50 * ABL:TARGET:戦闘能力
							DOWNBASE:MASTER:気力 += 50 * ABL:TARGET:戦闘能力
						ENDIF
				ENDSELECT
			CASE "parsee_house_vandalism"
				PRINTFORML You and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% wait for Parsee to leave her house, and then sneak in...
				SELECTCASE K60_ATTITUDE()
					;Loving
					CASE 0
						IF TALENT:60:恋人
							GOTO PARSEE_VANDALISM_LEWD_FAILURE
						ELSE
							PRINTFORML Only to see Parsee sitting at the table. \@CFLAG:[[パルスィ]]:K60EN_SEEN_TCS == 2 ? She must have left a clone to guard her house... # Wait, what? You saw her leave the house ten seconds ago! She can't stop time too, can she?\@
							PRINTFORML Parsee smiles at you and asks what you and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% are doing.
							PRINTFORML She'd be interested in joining you, if that's all right.
							PRINTFORML You stutter out that you were just visiting. Parsee thanks you and says she'll prepare some tea.
							PRINTFORML You and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% spend the next few hours chatting with Parsee and having tea.
							PRINTFORML To her credit, she only mentions being jealous of someone or something about a dozen times during your conversations.
							PRINTFORML It's not great, but it's progress.
							IF CFLAG:[[パルスィ]]:K60EN_SEEN_TCS == 2
								PRINTFORML Suddenly, she vanishes into thin air. You're startled at first, before you remember that she's a clone.
								PRINTFORML The door behind you opens and Parsee walks in. She tells you she's having Kisume over for drinks and invites you to join them.
								PRINTFORML You decline. You enjoy Parsee's company, especially now that she's suddenly started being nice to you...
								PRINTFORML But you didn't plan on spending the entire day chatting with her.
								PRINTFORML Besides, you'd rather not deal with a drunk hashihime.
								PRINTFORML She seems disappointed, but says she understands, and you and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% see yourselves out.
							ELSE
								PRINTFORML Suddenly, she mentions that she has something to do, and shoos you out of her house.
								PRINTFORML As you and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% walk towards the bridge, you see... Parsee, walking toward you.
								PRINTFORML She smiles and waves at you. You wave back, acting on instinct more than anything.
								PRINTFORML How is she doing this?! You're starting to get a headache now.
								DOWNBASE:MASTER:体力 += 20
							ENDIF
							PRINTFORML At least you and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% got some tea and a chance to practice your conversation skills.
							EXP:MASTER:会話経験 += 5
							EXP:CULPRIT:会話経験 += 5
						ENDIF
					;Nice, horny
					CASE 1
						$PARSEE_VANDALISM_LEWD_FAILURE
						PRINTFORML Only to see Parsee lying on the futon, legs spread, naked as the day she was born, and with a seductive grin on her face.
						PRINTFORML That grin quickly fades into a look of horror, no doubt matching your own.
						PRINTFORML As she screams and tries to cover herself up, you \@TALENT:CULPRIT:無知 ? cover %CALLNAME:CULPRIT%'s eyes and # and %CALLNAME:CULPRIT% \@ run out of her house as fast as you can.
						CALL UWAKI_RECORD(CULPRIT,0,60)
					CASE 2, 3 
						PRINTFORML Only to see Parsee sitting at the table. \@CFLAG:[[パルスィ]]:K60EN_SEEN_TCS == 2 ? She must have left a clone to guard the place... # Wait, what? You saw her leave the house ten seconds ago!\@
						PRINTFORML Parsee glares at you and tells you to get the hell out of her house.
						PRINTFORML You slink away, disappointed%COND_STR(" and very confused", CFLAG:[[パルスィ]]:K60EN_SEEN_TCS == 2)%.
				ENDSELECT
		ENDSELECT
		RETURN 1
	CASE "punishment"
		IF TALENT:TARGET:恋慕 && !MARK:TARGET:反発刻印 && !RAND:2
			TRYCALL Add_Forced_Date(TARGET, 10)
		ELSE
			$PARSEE_PUNISHMENT
			SELECTCASE RAND:3
				CASE 0
					PRINTFORML Parsee forces you to spend the whole day doing maintenance on her bridge.
					PRINTFORML Scrubbing it, repainting it, checking it for loose sections, fixing the loose sections... you're exhausted by the time you're done.
					DOWNBASE:MASTER:体力 += 400
					DOWNBASE:MASTER:気力 += 300
					TIME += 240
				CASE 1
				;Don't do the ushi no koku mairi punishment if Parsee's your lover or has a Loving/Horny attitude
					IF TALENT:TARGET:恋人
						GOTO PARSEE_PUNISHMENT
					ELSE
						SELECTCASE K60_ATTITUDE()
							CASE 0, 1
								GOTO PARSEE_PUNISHMENT
							CASE 2, 3
						ENDSELECT
					ENDIF
					PRINTFORML Parsee doesn't do anything to you at all. She just coldly tells you that you're going to pay for what you did and storms off.
					PRINTFORML You breathe a sigh of relief. You know how this goes.
					PRINTFORML You're supposed to spend the whole week terrified of what she's going to do to you...
					PRINTFORML Only for her to not do anything at all. The fear itself is the punishment.
					PRINTFORML You smirk to yourself and forget about her threat.
					CFLAG:[[パルスィ]]:K60EN_PARSEE_RAPE_REVENGE = 1
				CASE 2
					PRINTFORML Parsee forces you to spend the whole day at her house watching her hearth and making sure the fire doesn't go out.
					PRINTFORML She tells you that you can bring some things to distract yourself with, as long as you check on the fire every ten minutes or so.
					PRINTFORML She doesn't want you going mad from boredom. You can even borrow her art supplies as long as you don't make a mess.
					PRINTFORML You just need to set her alarm clock so you don't forget.
					PRINTFORML It's not much of a punishment, but you aren't going to complain.
					$DISTRACTION
					SELECTCASE RAND:2
						CASE 0
							IF !GROUPMATCH(1, MUSIC_ABLE(30), MUSIC_ABLE(31), MUSIC_ABLE(32), MUSIC_ABLE(33), MUSIC_ABLE(34), MUSIC_ABLE(35))
								GOTO DISTRACTION
							ELSE
								PRINTFORML You decide to hone your musical skills while watching the fire.
								EXP:MASTER:演奏経験 += 10
							ENDIF
						CASE 1
							PRINTFORML You decide to take Parsee up on her offer and do some painting while watching the fire.
					ENDSELECT
					PRINTFORML It turns out to be more of a punishment than you'd expected.
					PRINTFORML Every time you start getting into the groove of things, the alarm goes off, and you lose your focus.
					PRINTFORML On top of that, having to hear an alarm every ten minutes is starting to get to you.
					PRINTFORML By the time Parsee comes back and tells you you're done, your nerves are shot.
					PRINTFORML As you walk back home, you keep tensing up, expecting to hear an alarm clock ringing.
					PRINTFORML And when you do get home, it takes all of your willpower to avoid chucking your alarm clock out the window.
					TIME += 240
					DOWNBASE:MASTER:体力 += 300
					DOWNBASE:MASTER:気力 += 200
			ENDSELECT
		ENDIF
		RETURN 1
ENDSELECT
